Voidface browser demo — real code, no trained weights bundled.

Runs the shipped generator locally in the browser via
onnxruntime-web. WebGPU when the browser supports it; WASM fallback
otherwise. Files never leave the tab.

The demo needs a trained Voidface `.ort` or `.onnx` file. Produce
one with:

    voidface export runs/checkpoint.pt out/voidface.onnx \
        --quantize int8 --ort

Then load `out/voidface.ort` (or `out/voidface.int8.onnx`) via the
"Model" picker in the demo UI.

Development:

    cd tools/web
    npm install
    npm run dev

Production build:

    npm run build
    npm run preview

Design goals inherited from the top-level architecture:

  * No accounts. No telemetry. Nothing uploaded.
  * WebGPU when available; WASM fallback.
  * Input side lengths padded to a multiple of 16 before inference
    (matches the generator's stride constraint).

Files:

    index.html           Drop-target UI.
    src/main.ts          Model load + inference pipeline.
    vite.config.ts       Vite server with COOP/COEP headers.
    tsconfig.json        TypeScript strict.
    package.json         onnxruntime-web + Vite + TypeScript.

Not yet built:

  * Trained weight release (R5.5 — depends on real training run).
  * PWA install prompt.
  * Batch mode (multiple photos).
  * Video support.
